00:23:47,807 --> 00:23:51,731
Which reminded me of one of the biggest changes between Street Fighter 1 and Street Fighter 2

487
00:23:51,731 --> 00:23:56,976
when they introduced this slow motion after you beat your opponent.

488
00:23:56,976 --> 00:24:01,720
So you have that lingering effect of like seeing yourself beating or getting beaten.

489
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:05,964
So just that emotion is just much stronger.

490
00:24:05,964 --> 00:24:10,008
Which kind of also reminded me of one of my least favorite games in the world, Monopoly,

